    <title> Heart_murmur_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: HEART MURMUR (Clinical Finding)</h3>
      <!-- S: Setting -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Setting
          &amp; Status</span> <span class="verbal">"I understand a heart murmur
          has been found. Could you tell me how this was discovered? Was it
          during a routine check-up, or because you were feeling unwell?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs">Incidental finding vs. Found during investigation of
            symptoms</li>
          <li class="cvs">Is this a new murmur, or have you been told about it
            before?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms (THE CORE OF THE HISTORY) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"The most important
          thing is to understand how you have been feeling. Have you experienced
          any shortness of breath, chest pain, or dizziness?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="h4 cvs"><b>HEART FAILURE SYMPTOMS (Fluid Overload / Poor
              Output)</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="cvs respiratory"><b>Shortness of Breath (Dyspnea):</b>
                <ul>
                  <li>On exertion? (How many stairs? How far on the flat?)</li>
                  <li>When lying flat (Orthopnea)? (How many pillows do you
                    use?)</li>
                  <li>Waking you from sleep gasping for air (PND)?</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li class="cvs nephro"><b>Fluid Retention:</b> </li>
              <ul>
                <li class="cvs nephro">Swelling in your ankles or legs
                  (Peripheral Edema)? Abdominal bloating?</li>
                <li class="cvs nephro">ie., gain excessive weight?</li>
              </ul>
              <li class="cvs"><b>Fatigue:</b> Feeling unusually tired or having
                reduced exercise tolerance?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="h4 cvs emergency"><b>ISCHEMIA / INADEQUATE FLOW SYMPTOMS</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="cvs emergency"><b>Chest Pain / Angina:</b> Any
                tightness, pressure, or pain in your chest, especially on
                exertion?</li>
              <li class="cvs cns emergency"><b>Syncope / Pre-syncope:</b> Have
                you had any blackouts or dizzy spells, particularly when you
                exert yourself?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="h4 cvs cns infectious emergency"><b>EMBOLIC / INFECTIVE
              SYMPTOMS</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="cns emergency"><b>Neurological Events:</b> Any episodes
                of weakness, numbness, or speech disturbance (TIA/Stroke)?</li>
              <li class="infectious"><b>Constitutional Symptoms:</b> Unexplained
                fevers, chills, drenching night sweats, weight loss (Infective
                Endocarditis)?</li>
              <li class="infectious derma">Painful spots on fingers/toes,
                splinter hemorrhages under nails?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="h4 cvs"><b>OTHER SYMPTOMS</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="cvs">Palpitations (feeling your heart race or skip a
                beat)?</li>
              <li class="ent cns">Hoarseness of voice (can be due to left atrial
                enlargement compressing a nerve)?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Risk Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Risk
          Factors &amp; PMH</span> <span class="verbal">"I need to ask about
          your past health to understand the context of this murmur."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs">History of heart attack, hypertension, high
            cholesterol, or diabetes?</li>
          <li class="rheumatic infectious">History of <b><u>Rheumatic </u></b>Fever
            as a child?</li>
          <li class="cvs">Any congenital heart problems from birth (e.g., <b><u>bicuspid
                </u><u>aortic </u></b>valve)?</li>
          <li class="infectious emergency">History of IV <b><u>Drug </u></b>Use?</li>
          <li class="infectious">Recent <b><u>dental </u><u>procedures </u></b>or
            other infections?</li>
          <li class="cvs">Family history of <b><u>sudden </u><u>cardiac </u></b>death
            or valvular heart disease?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset
          (of Symptoms)</span> <span class="verbal">"When did you first start
          noticing any of these symptoms we've discussed?"</span> </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Have your symptoms been
          getting progressively worse over time?"</span> </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How has this been impacting your
          daily life? Has it stopped you from doing things you would normally
          do?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>(Clinician note: Quantify functional status, e.g., NYHA Class
            I-IV)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I'm just going to quickly
          summarize some of the key warning signs I'm looking for."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs cns emergency"><b>Syncope on exertion.</b></li>
          <li class="cvs emergency">New onset or rapidly worsening symptoms of
            heart failure.</li>
          <li class="infectious emergency">Signs of systemic infection (fever,
            night sweats) in the context of a new murmur (Infective
            Endocarditis).</li>
          <li class="cns emergency">Associated new neurological symptoms
            (suggesting an embolic event).</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Bother Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10,
          how much are these symptoms affecting your quality of life?"</span> </li>
    </div>
